description: Fighters from the Lebanese Hezbollah resistance movement have targeted an Israeli military base in the north of 1948 Israeli-occupied territories, amid exchanges of near-daily fire between the two sides since the occupying regime attacked Gaza, Press TV reported.
title: Hezbollah targets Israeli military base with heavy-caliber Burkan missile

description: Yemen's Ansarullah vowed on Sunday to continue targeting British ships in the Gulf of Aden following the sinking of UK-owned vessel Rubymar.
title: Yemen vows to continue targeting British ships

description: Hamas says Israel’s targeting of relief convoys, the latest of which was an aid truck in Deir el-Balah in the central Gaza Strip, is “an affirmation and insistence on its part to continue the war of genocide”, Al Jazeera reported.
title: Hamas: Israel’s targeting of Deir el-Balah aid truck is ‘insistence on genocide’

description: Pakistan's newly formed parliament elected Shehbaz Sharif as prime minister for a second term.
title: Shehbaz Sharif wins second term as Pakistan PM

description: A series of explosions have rocked Crimea, after a reported Ukrainian drone attack on the peninsula which was annexed by Russia in 2014.
title: Russia says it intercepts 38 Ukrainian drones attacking Crimea

description: TEHRAN- The Deputy of the Army Ground Forces has announced a significant milestone in the ongoing efforts to clear landmines and unexploded ordnance from Iran's border regions.
title: Over five million landmines cleared from contaminated border areas: commander

description: TEHRAN- The Venezuelan Minister of Foreign Affairs has expressed congratulations to the Iranian government and nation over the successful holding of the elections on behalf of President Nicolas Maduro as well as the Latin American nation’s government.
title: Venezuela FM hails Iran elections

description: TEHRAN- The Leader of the Islamic Revolution, Ayatollah Seyed Ali Khamenei, expressed his condolences in a message on the demise of Ayatollah Hajj Sheikh Muhammad Emami Kashani (ra) on Sunday.
title: Leader condoles demise of Ayatollah Emami Kashani

description: TEHRAN- The commander of the Islamic Revolution Guards Corps (IRGC) has highlighted the failure of the enemy in the economic battleground, emphasizing that the Khatam-al Anbiya Construction Headquarters successfully thwarted the enemy's economic warfare plot.
title: Economic conspiracies foiled by Khatam-al Anbiya Construction Headquarters: IRGC chief

description: TEHRAN - Mohsen Eslami, the spokesperson for Iran's Election Headquarters, provided further insights into the process of the second round of elections in Tehran during a briefing on Sunday.
title: Spokesperson details preparations for parliamentary run-off

description: TEHRAN- Sher Mohammad Abbas Stanikzai, the political deputy minister of the caretaker government of Afghanistan (Taliban), has emphasized that the Islamic Emirate is committed to ensuring Iran’s water rights according to the 1973 treaty.
title: Taliban official says committed to honoring Iran water rights

description: TEHRAN – Iranian President Ebrahim Raisi has called upon mosques across Muslim nations to shed light on the dire situation faced by oppressed Palestinians in the Gaza Strip amid the Israeli aggression.
title: Iranian president calls on mosques to raise global awareness on Gaza crisis

description: TEHRAN- Palestinian organizations have called on the international community to enforce an energy embargo on the Israeli regime to pressure Tel Aviv to end its genocidal campaign against the people of Gaza.
title: Calls for global energy embargo on Tel Aviv

description: TEHRAN-Six Iranian short films will go on screen at the Fribourg International Film Festival, which will be held in the Swiss city from March 17 to 26.
title: Iranian shorts line up for Fribourg Intl. Film Festival

description: TEHRAN-The Cinema Museum of Iran, in north of Tehran, will screen the restored version of the famous 1987 Iranian feature film “Captain Khorshid” written and directed by Nasser Taghvai on Wednesday.
title: Cinema Museum of Iran to show restored version of Taghvai’s “Captain Khorshid”

description: TEHRAN-Four Iranian illustrators are among the winners of the 58th Illustrators Exhibition of the 61st Bologna Children Book Fair (BCBF), which is due to be held from April 8 to 11 in Bologna, Italy.
title: 4 Iranian illustrators among Bologna Children Book Fair Illustrators Exhibition winners

description: TEHRAN- The 35th Tehran International Book Fair (TIBF) is scheduled to take place at Tehran's Imam Khomeini Mosalla from May 18 to 28, the book fair's deputy director has said.
title: 2024 Tehran Intl. Book Fair to be held in Tehran’s Mosalla

description: TEHRAN- Since Israel launched war on the Gaza Strip nearly five months ago, it has perpetrated massacre after massacre and used starvation of civilians as a method of warfare in the besieged Palestinian territory.
title: Starvation as a Weapon: Gaza Tragedy

description: TEHRAN - Iran on Sunday executed a Mossad agent who had tried to blow up a workshop complex of the Defense Ministry with drones in the central city of Isfahan on January 28, 2023.
title: Mossad agent executed for 2023 Israeli attack on military site in Isfahan

description:
Thousands of Palestinians are reported to be at risk of starvation and thirst in the Gaza Strip as Israeli attacks continue.

It is becoming increasingly difficult to find food in the town of Rafah, where tens of thousands of Palestinians fleeing the attacks have taken refuge. Food cooked on wood fires by volunteers has been distributed to Gazans sheltering in the town.
title: Gaza suffers on brink of hunger and thirst

description: TEHRAN – Iranian woman sprinter Maryam Toosi won a silver medal on Saturday during the final day of the Beach Opener held Jack Rose Track in Long Beach, Calif.
title: Iran’s Toosi takes silver at Beach Opener 200 meters

description: TEHRAN – As a priceless measure, four authentic elements, found in Kermanshah province, have been enshrined in Iran’s national heritage roster.
title: Coins, cylindrical seal, wooden door and processional standard named national heritage

description: TEHRAN – Tehran is set to host a regional conference on safeguarding intangible cultural heritage in early March.
title: Tehran to host intangible heritage conference

description: TEHRAN - The ancient city of Yazd, recently designated as the tourism capital of the Asia Cooperation Dialogue (ACD) for 2024, is set to welcome 14 ambassadors and representatives from member countries.
title: ACD representatives invited to Yazd

description: TEHRAN – With the new visa exemptions in place, now is the perfect time for travelers to seize the opportunity to uncover the wonders of Iran and create unforgettable memories that will last a lifetime.
title: A first-timer’s guide to Iran: when to visit, things to do

description: Embark on a journey towards refined city living as Audleys International introduces The Haydon, an opulent apartment building situated in the heart of London's Square Mile. More than just a residence, The Haydon emerges as a unique urban oasis, offering an unparalleled lifestyle immersed in the cultural richness of the city. For those considering buying property in London, The Haydon stands as a beacon of sophistication, seamlessly blending architectural prowess with lavish amenities.
title: The Haydon: Luxurious Living in London's Square Mile

description: TEHRAN – Iran discovered their opponents at the 10th edition of the Asian Men’s Youth Handball Championship.
title: Iran learn fate at 2024 Asian Men’s Youth Handball Championship

description: TEHRAN – The first International Congress on Family Health will open in Tehran on Tuesday to publicize the important role of family health in society.
title: Tehran conference to turn spotlight on family health

description: TEHRAN – Iran and Russia will soon establish a joint innovation center, the deputy science minister has said.
title: Tehran, Moscow to set up joint innovation center

description: TEHRAN –World Wildlife Day is celebrated annually on March 3 to raise awareness of the multitude of benefits that wildlife conservation provides to people and the significance of preserving endangered species from dying out.
title: Let's save unique species from the brink of extinction

description: TEHRAN - Iran’s Trade Promotion Organization (TPO) held a conference on Syria’s trade opportunities for Iranian business operators on Sunday, RINA reported.
title: Tehran hosts Iran-Syria trade conference

description: TEHRAN- During the past Iranian calendar week (ended on Friday), Iran Mercantile Exchange (IME) witnessed trade of 3,112,323 tons of commodities with a total trading value of nearly $804 million, posting growths of four percent and 21 percent in volume and value of trades compared with the week before that.
title: Commodities worth over $800m traded at IME in a week

description: TEHRAN- Non-oil products worth $1.322 billion were exported from Isfahan province during the first 11 months of the current Iranian calendar year (March 21, 2023-February 19, 2024), the director-general of the province’s Customs Department announced.
title: Commodities worth over $1.3b exported from Isfahan province in 11 months

description: TEHRAN- Transit of commodities through Iran increased by 35 percent during the first 11 months of the current Iranian calendar year (March 21, 2023-February 19, 2024), as compared to the same period of time in the past year, according to the data released by the Islamic Republic of Iran Customs Administration (IRICA).
title: Transit of goods via Iran rises 35% in 11 months on year

description: TEHRAN- TEDPIX, the main index of the Tehran Stock Exchange (TSE), rose 60,470 points (2.9 percent) to 2,147,010 on Sunday, which is the second day of the Iranian calendar week.
title: TEDPIX rises 60,000 points on Sunday

description: TEHRAN - Iranian Oil Minister Javad Oji met with his counterparts from Iraq, Angola, Russia, and Venezuela in separate meetings on Saturday.
title: Oji holds talks with counterparts during GECF summit

description: TEHRAN – Hadi Choopan won the 2024 Arnold Classic, proving he remains the number one contender for the Mr. Olympia title.
title: Hadi Choopan wins 2024 Arnold Classic
